Let $x$ be the number of words I learn. Suppose I get $85$% on the exam. Then, of the $500$ words on the exam, there are $\frac{85}{100}\cdot500=425$ words that I will recall. This is the same as having $425$ correct guesses out of $x$ words I learned, so
\begin{align*}
\frac{x}{x}=425.\\
\end{align*}
Let $y$ be the number of correct guesses and $x$ the number of words I learned. I recall correctly that \begin{align*}
\frac{y}{x}&=85 \\
\frac{85}{100}&=\frac{425}{x}.\\
\end{align*}
So I must learn at least $\frac{425}{0.85}=500$ words. However, I can possibly recall more words by guessing.
Therefore, $$\boxed{\text{I should learn at least 500 words.}}$$
